---
import Dashboard from '../../layouts/Dashboard.astro';
---

<Dashboard title="Docs: Presets" activeNav="docs">
  <div class="max-w-3xl space-y-4">
    <p class="text-gray-700">
      Presets are named collections of theme setting values (colors, typography, etc.).
      Preset definitions live in <code class="px-1 py-0.5 bg-gray-100 rounded">library/presets</code>.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm border border-gray-200 p-6">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">How it works</h2>
      <div class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <p>Applying a preset updates project settings data so previews and exports reflect the new values.</p>
        <p>Presets should be designed to be compatible with the base theme settings schema.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm border border-gray-200 p-6">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Best practices</h2>
      <div class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <p>Version presets carefully; changing meaning of existing keys can cause surprising project diffs.</p>
        <p>Keep presets small and intentional, not exhaustive.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Dashboard>
